							"authorNames": "Xinghua Qu (Tianqiao and Chrissy Chen Institute, Singapore), Zhu Sun (CFAR, IHPC, A*STAR, Singapore), Shanshan Feng (CFAR, IHPC, A*STAR, Singapore), Caishun Chen (CFAR, IHPC, A*STAR, Singapore), Tian Tian (University of California, United States)",
							"abstract": "Most emotional support conversations (ESCs) currently rely on text-based interfaces, which may not be user-friendly, especially for individuals with visual impairments or those who struggle with reading and writing. Thus, we present a personalized voice-based ESC system powered by large language models (LLMs). It can analyze emotional status from vocal user inputs, which provides deep insights that text-based methods cannot, enabling the LLM-driven chatbot to offer more tailored and effective emotional support to its users. Our code is available at https://github.com/xinghua-qu/speech_emotion_recognition",
							"searchText": "2024 IEEE Conference on Artificial Intelligence (CAI) CAI 2024 Breaking the Silence: Whisper-Driven Emotion Recognition in AI Mental Support Models 1713147254811 10.1109/CAI59869.2024.00063 Xinghua Qu Tianqiao and Chrissy Chen Institute, Singapore quxinghua17@gmail.com Zhu Sun CFAR, IHPC, A*STAR, Singapore n/a Shanshan Feng CFAR, IHPC, A*STAR, Singapore feng_shanshan@cfar.a-star.edu.sg Caishun Chen CFAR, IHPC, A*STAR, Singapore chen_caishun@cfar.a-star.edu.sg Tian Tian University of California, United States liltian@ucdavis.edu Mental Healthcare AI for Social Good Large Language Models Voice-based Emotional Support Conversation Most emotional support conversations (ESCs) currently rely on text-based interfaces, which may not be user-friendly, especially for individuals with visual impairments or those who struggle with reading and writing. Thus, we present a personalized voice-based ESC system powered by large language models (LLMs). It can analyze emotional status from vocal user inputs, which provides deep insights that text-based methods cannot, enabling the LLM-driven chatbot to offer more tailored and effective emotional support to its users. Our code is available at https://github.com/xinghua-qu/speech_emotion_recognition",
