							"abstract": "The Vision Transformer has been a more effective architecture for computer vision tasks than convolutional neural networks (CNN). However, it is time-consuming due to the quadratic complexity of the input sequence length. In this paper, a Fast Vision Transformer (FViT) is proposed based on an additive attention module, which reduces computation complexity to linearity. The experiment results show that the proposed model achieves faster inference with less memory. ",
							"searchText": "2024 IEEE Conference on Artificial Intelligence (CAI) CAI 2024 Fast Vision Transformer via Additive Attention 1714041923659 10.1109/CAI59869.2024.00113 Yang Wen Shenzhen University, China n/a Samuel Chen Xidian Univerisity, China n/a Abhishek Krishna Shrestha Xidian Univerisity, China n/a Fast Vision Transformer Additive Attention The Vision Transformer has been a more effective architecture for computer vision tasks than convolutional neural networks (CNN). However, it is time-consuming due to the quadratic complexity of the input sequence length. In this paper, a Fast Vision Transformer (FViT) is proposed based on an additive attention module, which reduces computation complexity to linearity. The experiment results show that the proposed model achieves faster inference with less memory.",
