							"text": "Gated Self-Supervised Learning for Improving Supervised Learning",
							"articleLocation": "pdfs/CAI2024-2fo5urY39gdhGmFJimhucB/540900a618/540900a618.pdf",
							"extraLocations": [],
							"authorNames": "Erland Hilman Fuadi (Brawijaya University, Indonesia), Aristo Renaldo Ruslim (Brawijaya University, Indonesia), Putu Wahyu Kusuma Wardhana (Brawijaya University, Indonesia), Novanto Yudistira (Brawijaya University, Indonesia)",
							"abstract": "In past research on self-supervised learning for image classification, the use of rotation as an augmentation has been common. However, relying solely on rotation as a self-supervised transformation can limit the ability of the model to learn rich features from the data. In this paper, we propose a novel approach to self-supervised learning for image classification using several localizable augmentations with the combination of the gating method. Our approach uses flip and shuffle channel augmentations in addition to the rotation, allowing the model to learn rich features from the data. Furthermore, the gated mixture network is used to weigh the effects of each self-supervised learning on the loss function, allowing the model to focus on the most relevant transformations for classification.",
							"searchText": "2024 IEEE Conference on Artificial Intelligence (CAI) CAI 2024 Gated Self-Supervised Learning for Improving Supervised Learning 1714001265454 10.1109/CAI59869.2024.00120 Erland Hilman Fuadi Brawijaya University, Indonesia erland313@student.ub.ac.id Aristo Renaldo Ruslim Brawijaya University, Indonesia aristo1renaldo@student.ub.ac.id Putu Wahyu Kusuma Wardhana Brawijaya University, Indonesia wahyukusuma29@student.ub.ac.id Novanto Yudistira Brawijaya University, Indonesia yudistira@ub.ac.id self-supervised learning supervised learning transformations mixture of expert gating network In past research on self-supervised learning for image classification, the use of rotation as an augmentation has been common. However, relying solely on rotation as a self-supervised transformation can limit the ability of the model to learn rich features from the data. In this paper, we propose a novel approach to self-supervised learning for image classification using several localizable augmentations with the combination of the gating method. Our approach uses flip and shuffle channel augmentations in addition to the rotation, allowing the model to learn rich features from the data. Furthermore, the gated mixture network is used to weigh the effects of each self-supervised learning on the loss function, allowing the model to focus on the most relevant transformations for classification.",
