							"text": "Real-time Scheduling Optimization with Deep Learning-Powered Demand Forecasting in Water Transportation",
							"articleLocation": "pdfs/CAI2024-2fo5urY39gdhGmFJimhucB/540900b166/540900b166.pdf",
							"extraLocations": [],
							"authorNames": "Wang Yukuan (Wuhan University of Technology, China), Liu Jingxian (Wuhan University of Technology, China), Zhang Jiayi (Wuhan University of Technology, China), Yu Hongchu (Wuhan University of Technology, China), Di Zhongjie (Wuhan University of Technology, China)",
							"abstract": "The notable demand volatility in water transportation often lead to capacity shortages or deficits for passengers and roll-on/roll-off ship. Thus, how to enhance the quality of port operations using artificial intelligence (AI) technology? We proposed a two-stage real-time scheduling optimization approach, which comprises a prediction model based on deep learning and a scheduling decision module grounded in expert rules. Two key innovations are involved (1): Thoroughly leveraging relevant data concerning transportation demand by utilizing a Temporal Fusion Transformer (TFT) for demand prediction. (2): Establishing a scheduling optimizer based on long-term expert rules to match the flight schedules with future 2-3 hours of demand. Case study validate that the application of AI in port scheduling significantly elevates the quality of transportation services and economic efficiency.",
							"searchText": "2024 IEEE Conference on Artificial Intelligence (CAI) CAI 2024 Real-time Scheduling Optimization with Deep Learning-Powered Demand Forecasting in Water Transportation 1715223787399 10.1109/CAI59869.2024.00209 Wang Yukuan Wuhan University of Technology, China wang_yk@whut.edu.cn Liu Jingxian Wuhan University of Technology, China n/a Zhang Jiayi Wuhan University of Technology, China n/a Yu Hongchu Wuhan University of Technology, China n/a Di Zhongjie Wuhan University of Technology, China n/a water transportation scheduling optimization demand prediction deep learning temporal fusion transformer The notable demand volatility in water transportation often lead to capacity shortages or deficits for passengers and roll-on/roll-off ship. Thus, how to enhance the quality of port operations using artificial intelligence (AI) technology? We proposed a two-stage real-time scheduling optimization approach, which comprises a prediction model based on deep learning and a scheduling decision module grounded in expert rules. Two key innovations are involved (1): Thoroughly leveraging relevant data concerning transportation demand by utilizing a Temporal Fusion Transformer (TFT) for demand prediction. (2): Establishing a scheduling optimizer based on long-term expert rules to match the flight schedules with future 2-3 hours of demand. Case study validate that the application of AI in port scheduling significantly elevates the quality of transportation services and economic efficiency.",
