							"authorNames": "Mohammed Ayalew Belay (Norwegian University of Science and Technology, Norway), Adil Rasheed (Norwegian University of Science and Technology, Norway), Pierluigi Salvo Rossi (SINTEF Energy Research, Norway)",
							"abstract": "In this paper, we propose a novel modular architecture for self-supervised multi-sensor anomaly detection and localization. The framework consists of a spatio-temporal encoder for representation learning, a decoder for latent reconstruction, a predictive memory network for sub-sequence pattern identification, and a denoiser for false-positive reduction. It uniquely combines a reconstruction and latent prediction network and optimizes the modules in an end-to-end mechanism to minimize the combined weighted loss. We demonstrate the flexibility and efficiency of our architecture by introducing different components for each module, showcasing its adaptability and enhanced performance in anomaly detection and localization.",
							"searchText": "2024 IEEE Conference on Artificial Intelligence (CAI) CAI 2024 Self-Supervised Modular Architecture for Multi-Sensor Anomaly Detection and Localization 1713979363202 10.1109/CAI59869.2024.00226 Mohammed Ayalew Belay Norwegian University of Science and Technology, Norway mohammed.a.belay@ntnu.no Adil Rasheed Norwegian University of Science and Technology, Norway adil.rasheed@ntnu.no Pierluigi Salvo Rossi SINTEF Energy Research, Norway salvorossi@ieee.org Multi-sensor anomaly detection self-supervised learning and anomaly localization In this paper, we propose a novel modular architecture for self-supervised multi-sensor anomaly detection and localization. The framework consists of a spatio-temporal encoder for representation learning, a decoder for latent reconstruction, a predictive memory network for sub-sequence pattern identification, and a denoiser for false-positive reduction. It uniquely combines a reconstruction and latent prediction network and optimizes the modules in an end-to-end mechanism to minimize the combined weighted loss. We demonstrate the flexibility and efficiency of our architecture by introducing different components for each module, showcasing its adaptability and enhanced performance in anomaly detection and localization.",
