							"eid": "4lLQmZNUBBVtMmXeEK8His",
							"type": "authorPaper",
							"text": "Talking Face Generation via Face Mesh - Controllability Without Reference Videos",
							"articleLocation": "pdfs/CAI2024-2fo5urY39gdhGmFJimhucB/540900b373/540900b373.pdf",
							"extraLocations": [],
							"authorNames": "Ali Koksal (Agency for Science, Technology and Research (A*STAR), Singapore), Qianli Xu (Agency for Science, Technology and Research (A*STAR), Singapore), Joo Hwee Lim (Agency for Science, Technology and Research (A*STAR), Singapore)",
							"abstract": "Recent development in audio-driven talking face generation strives for controlling facial features including facial expression, head pose, eye blink, etc. as well as accurate lipsynchronization and the ability to apply to arbitrary subjects. Existing audio-visual models that can control facial features require encoders that encode driving videos, which is both computationally expensive and limited by the availability of such driving videos. In this paper, we address this limitation and aim to control facial features without encoding driving videos. We propose a cascaded GAN-based audio-visual model, which incorporates face mesh as an intermediate representation. Different from existing cascaded methods that use facial landmarks, our method uses face mesh as a medium of informative facial feature representation. To the best of our knowledge, this is the first cascaded model that allows controllable talking face generation via face mesh. We train our audio-visual model with training samples of MEAD dataset. In the evaluation, we benchmark our model in extensive experiments on MEAD and LRW datasets. The results show our model outperforms existing ones by generating high-fidelity audio-driven talking faces on arbitrary subjects with realistic emotional expression patterns.",
							"searchText": "2024 IEEE Conference on Artificial Intelligence (CAI) CAI 2024 Talking Face Generation via Face Mesh - Controllability Without Reference Videos 1713775521043 10.1109/CAI59869.2024.00246 Ali Koksal Agency for Science, Technology and Research (A*STAR), Singapore koksal_ali@i2r.a-star.edu.sg Qianli Xu Agency for Science, Technology and Research (A*STAR), Singapore qxu@i2r.a-star.edu.sg Joo Hwee Lim Agency for Science, Technology and Research (A*STAR), Singapore joohwee@i2r.a-star.edu.sg talking face generation facial animation controllable generation Recent development in audio-driven talking face generation strives for controlling facial features including facial expression, head pose, eye blink, etc. as well as accurate lipsynchronization and the ability to apply to arbitrary subjects. Existing audio-visual models that can control facial features require encoders that encode driving videos, which is both computationally expensive and limited by the availability of such driving videos. In this paper, we address this limitation and aim to control facial features without encoding driving videos. We propose a cascaded GAN-based audio-visual model, which incorporates face mesh as an intermediate representation. Different from existing cascaded methods that use facial landmarks, our method uses face mesh as a medium of informative facial feature representation. To the best of our knowledge, this is the first cascaded model that allows controllable talking face generation via face mesh. We train our audio-visual model with training samples of MEAD dataset. In the evaluation, we benchmark our model in extensive experiments on MEAD and LRW datasets. The results show our model outperforms existing ones by generating high-fidelity audio-driven talking faces on arbitrary subjects with realistic emotional expression patterns.",
